===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|nedle|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|nædl|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*nēþlō}}, from pre-Germanic {{term/t|en|*neh₁-tleh₂}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*(s)néh₁}}- ‘to spin, twist’ (compare Dutch {{term|naaien|lang=nl}}, Welsh {{term|nyddu|lang=cy}}, Latin {{term/t|la|nēre}}, Sanskrit {{term||snāyati}} ‘wraps up, winds’). Related to {{l|en|snood}}.

